OL,3,C'I would have probably punched' Ofsted
OL,4,Cstaff, says education secretary
OL,6,FIn his first major speech since
OL,7,Fbecoming chief inspector, Sir Martyn
OL,8,Ftold headteachers that he wanted to
OL,9,F"mark a new chapter" with the sector,
OL,10,Fadding that "nothing is off the table".
OL,12,FHe said: "I have been clear with my
OL,13,Fteams that they must go about their
OL,14,Fwork with professionalism, empathy,
OL,15,Fcourtesy and respect. And I hope, in
OL,16,Fturn, our inspectors will be received
OL,17,Fwith the same.
OL,19,F"I want to calm any tensions and
OL,20,Freduce any friction that has built up
OL,21,Fin recent months."
